cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is about person re-identification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a deep learning architecture for feature learning, which involves training a neural network to extract discriminative features from images. This falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves experiments on datasets, which falls under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper proposes a novel approach for local feature representation, which involves partitioning images into stripes, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves evaluating the performance of the proposed method against existing approaches, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
